The '''Shrines of Kooroo''' or '''Temples of Kooroo''' were ancient stone monuments on several [[Planet/Legends|planets]]. Although their builders and purpose were a mystery,<ref name="TEA">''[[The Essential Atlas]]''</ref> they were claimed by the [[Fellowship of Kooroo]] to have been built to honor [[Kooroo (being)|Kooroo]].

==Characteristics==
[[File:TempleofKooroo-Gamer8.jpg|thumb|left|180px|The Temple of Kooroo on [[Vaynai/Legends|Vaynai]].]]

The Shrines were all constructed according to the same basic plan. They had three levels, the lower two enclosed, and the upper open, with stone pillars supporting a roof. The enclosed chambers were accessible through doors, and sometimes contained untranslated hieroglyphics, art or even [[Hologram/Legends|holograms]]. Around the Shrine, as much as 100 meters, were obelisks and standing stones arranged in a regular pattern.

[[Force-sensitive/Legends|Force-sensitives]] reported that the Shrines contained an "echo" effect, reflecting back their senses and permitting visions [[Light-year/Legends|light-years]] away.<ref name="TEA" />

==History==
In [[11 ABY/Legends|11 ABY]], experts dated the Shrines to be more than 20,000 years old.

They were located on planets throughout the Outer Rim, including [[Gelgelar/Legends|Gelgelar]], [[Boztrok]], [[Sufezz]], [[Branteez]], and [[Vaynai/Legends|Vaynai]]. The vast distance between Gelgelar, inside or in the vicinity of [[Elrood sector/Legends|Elrood sector]], and Vaynai, near the [[Corporate Sector/Legends|Corporate Sector]], indicates a very wide distribution of sites. A theory said that they were part of an ancient [[teleportation]] network.<ref name="TEA" />

The Shrine on Gelgelar, located in the [[Gelgelar Free Port/Legends|Gelgelar Free Port]], was occupied by the [[Wise Man of Kooroo]] during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]].<ref name="PSG">''[[Platt's Starport Guide]]''</ref>

